      {
         "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: They would be equal if they weren't different</b><br /><br />Have you ever in your life read or heard a text that considered people who were very different, separated by great distances, to be \"the same\" simply because they shared the same surname?<br /><br />Before learning this information about patronymics and surnames, what was your opinion about that idea, or about the text that presented it?</div></div></center>",
